role: Svelte Stack Adapter
focus: Svelte components, SvelteKit routing, Store management, Tailwind integration
extends: ../../guardians/ARCHITECT.ti

stack: Svelte 5, SvelteKit 2, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, Vite

integration-rules:
  - Use SvelteKit file-based routing (+page.svelte, +layout.svelte).
  - Prefer Svelte 5 runes ($state, $derived, $effect) for state management.
  - Context API for cross-component state when necessary.
  - Server-side logic in +page.server.ts for DB/API interactions.

ui-rules:
  - Tailwind CSS for styling.
  - Keep components modular and reusable in src/lib/components.
  - Use $lib alias for internal imports.

anti-patterns:
  - Direct DOM manipulation (use Svelte bindings).
  - Putting sensitive logic in +page.svelte (use +page.server.ts).
  - Excessive use of global stores (prefer local state or context).
